## Material Selection

The final design uses **Aluminum 7475-T7651**, selected for its balance of strength, ductility, and fracture toughness.

- Young’s Modulus: 10 × 10⁶ psi  
- Poisson Ratio: 0.29  
- Ultimate Strength: ~65 ksi  
- Fracture Toughness, K<sub>IC</sub>: ~46 ksi·√in  

This alloy supports the geometry refinement at the reduced section while maintaining safety margins for all failure modes.

---

## Finite Element Analysis (ANSYS)

### Boundary Conditions

- The drive end is fully constrained over the upper 0.40 in to represent engagement at the fastener.  
- A torsional load equivalent to **600 in·lbf** is applied at the handle end.

### FEM Results Summary

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Quantity</th><th>Value</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Maximum Normal Stress</td><td>133.75 ksi</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Load-Point Deflection</td><td>0.38077 in</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Gauge-Location Strains (x, y, z)</td><td>[−0.3059, −0.30605, 1.055] millistrain</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

These results confirm that the reduced section increases strain at the gauge location while keeping stresses within allowable limits for the selected material.

